                        <title xml:lang="en">Commentary on Job </title>
                        
                        
                        
                        <note>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>This portions of the manuscript contains Job 1:6, 2:8-10, 3:1-3, 10-11, 3:25-4:1, 5:25-6:25, 11:10-11, 11:!5-12:8, 12:21-24, 13:27-14:5, 24:11-22, 15:2-3, 5-14, 16:19-21, 20:4-11, 29:1-4, 31:7-32:8, 32:14-33:30, 34:5-9, 20-37, 35:8-15, 36:3-21, 25-28, 36:32-37:24, 38:12-32, 37-40, 40:19-41:19, both the Hebrew text and Yefet's translation with commentary.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>The Hebrew text is written in Arabic characters and provided with the Hebrew vowel-points and accents in red.</p>
                           
                           
                           
                           <p>The method of transcription from Hebrew to Arabic is phonetic.</p>
                        
                        
                        
                        </note>
                     
                     
                     
